<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,1066,1492]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
COMMENTS. The lingular apex of this species is atypical for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martin" authorityYear="2008" box="[957,1097,1267,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Aleurodicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[957,1097,1267,1292]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Aleurodicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, being narrowly acute, its 4 setae situated very close to the apex (Fig. 16). The subtle reticulate patterning of the cuticle in the cephalothorax and abdominal subdorsum (Figs 14, 15), seen in many specimens, is also unusual as is the sometimes extensive dark, cloudy cuticular pigmentation seen in some individual puparia. 
<taxonomicName box="[1116,1338,1387,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Aleurodicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugioperculatus">
<emphasis box="[1116,1338,1387,1412]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">A. rugioperculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[269,377,1427,1452]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Aleurodicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niveus">
<emphasis box="[269,377,1427,1452]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">A. niveus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(also described from 
<collectingCountry box="[631,707,1426,1452]" name="Belize" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Belize</collectingCountry>
) and may be distinguished from it by use of the key to species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martin" authorityYear="2008" box="[182,322,1467,1492]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Aleurodicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[182,322,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Aleurodicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, couplets 30-31, p. 19.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
